sql:
SELECT SUM(on_hand) AS total_quantity_on_hand
FROM inventory_levels
WHERE item_code = '1';

SELECT i.item_name, il.on_hand
FROM items i
JOIN inventory_levels il ON i.item_code = il.item_code;

external_knowledge:
- "major category" refers to the top-level categories or any categories in the hierarchical structure;
- "overall available" means the total on-hand stock quantity;
- "pending" refers to the total quantity of items currently on order;
- "reserved" means the total quantity of items allocated to outstanding orders;
- "financial values" include the total market values of available, pending, and reserved stock, calculated by multiplying the respective quantities by their selling prices.

sql:
SELECT SUM(quantity) AS total_quantity
FROM inventory_transactions
WHERE transaction_type = 'Issue';

SELECT warehouse_id, on_hand
FROM inventory_levels
WHERE on_hand < 100;
